Here's a C program to print a 4-level pyramid:

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int rows = 4;

    for (int i = 1; i <= rows; i++) {
        // Print spaces
        for (int j = 1; j <= rows - i; j++) {
            printf(" ");
        }

        // Print stars
        for (int k = 1; k <= 2 * i - 1; k++) {
            printf("*");
        }

        printf("\n");
    }

    return 0;
}
```

Output:
```
   *
  ***
 *****
*******
```

The program uses nested loops: the outer loop controls rows, the first inner loop prints leading spaces, and the second inner loop prints the stars. Each row has `2*i - 1` stars where `i` is the row number.

Here's a clean JSX component for displaying a soccer match score:

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import './MatchScore.css'; // Optional for styling

const MatchScore = ({ homeTeam, awayTeam, homeScore, awayScore, status }) => {
  return (
    <div className="match-score">
      <div className="team home">
        <span className="team-name">{homeTeam}</span>
        <span className="team-score">{homeScore}</span>
      </div>
      <div className="status">
        <span className="match-status">{status}</span>
      </div>
      <div className="team away">
        <span className="team-score">{awayScore}</span>
        <span className="team-name">{awayTeam}</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default MatchScore;
```

**Usage example:**
```jsx
<MatchScore
  homeTeam="Manchester United"
  awayTeam="Liverpool"
  homeScore={2}
  awayScore={1}
  status="FT" // or "HT", "15'", "POSTPONED", etc.
/>
```

**Optional minimal CSS (`MatchScore.css`):**
```css
.match-score {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding: 12px;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  border: 1px solid #eee;
  border-radius: 8px;
  background: #f9f9f9;
}

.team {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 4px;
}

.team-name {
  font-weight: bold;
  font-size: 14px;
}

.team-score {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: bold;
  color: #333;
}

.status {
  font-weight: bold;
  font-size: 16px;
  color: #666;
  margin: 0 16px;
}

.home .team-score { color: #d32f2f; }
.away .team-score { color: #1976d2; }
```

This component is reusable, accessible, and easily stylable.
